    pearls: ["The 2014 ILAE definition allows epilepsy diagnosis after a SINGLE unprovoked seizure if recurrence risk is ≥60% (structural lesion on MRI or epileptiform EEG) -- two unprovoked seizures are no longer required","A normal interictal EEG does NOT exclude epilepsy -- up to 50% of patients have a normal first EEG; sleep deprivation and repeat recording increase diagnostic yield","Carbamazepine and phenytoin can WORSEN absence and myoclonic seizures in idiopathic generalized epilepsy -- always classify seizure type before selecting an ASM","Drug-resistant epilepsy is defined as failure of two appropriately chosen and tolerated ASMs -- refer early for presurgical evaluation as temporal lobe surgery has 60-80% seizure-freedom rates","Valproate is contraindicated in women of childbearing potential due to neural tube defects and neurodevelopmental delay -- lamotrigine and levetiracetam are preferred alternatives"],
