    pearls: ["PICO is the foundation of EBP: Population (Who?), Intervention (What treatment/exposure?), Comparison (Compared to what?), Outcome (What result?) — every answerable clinical question can be structured this way","NNT (Number Needed to Treat) is the most clinically meaningful statistic: it tells you how many patients need to receive the intervention for one additional patient to benefit; NNT of 1 is perfect, NNT of 100 means minimal benefit","The hierarchy of evidence: Level I (systematic reviews/meta-analyses of RCTs) > Level II (single RCTs) > Level III (controlled trials without randomization) > Level IV (cohort/case-control studies) > Level V (systematic reviews of descriptive studies) > Level VI (single descriptive studies) > Level VII (expert opinion)","Statistical significance (p <0.05) does NOT equal clinical significance — a drug that lowers blood pressure by 1 mmHg may be statistically significant with a large sample size but is clinically meaningless","The Iowa Model Revised is the most widely used EBP implementation framework in nursing: it guides the process from identifying a clinical trigger through forming a team, appraising evidence, implementing the change, and evaluating outcomes"],
